    <title role="Reserved Ports">Reserved Ports</title>

<para>A socket refers to a port on a specific location specified by the
IP address. Internet communication requires an IP address and a
port on the computer located at the specified IP address. There are
65,536 ports available on each machine. Some of these are reserved
for standard protocols:</para>

