<para><emphasis>FTP</emphasis> is used to download files from the internet. <emphasis>Telnet</emphasis>
supports remote login into a machine. <emphasis>SMTP</emphasis> is used to
transport mail and <emphasis>POP</emphasis> to store mail and to deliver it to
mail servers. <emphasis>HTTP</emphasis> is used for hypertext (Web) documents.</para>

<para>You should of course avoid these common ports for your
applications/applets except when specifically writing applications
for these (<abbrev>e.g.</abbrev> web servers, web browsers, ftp servers, ...). It
is generally recommended that you use ports in the range between
4000 and 8000 for your non-standard TCP/IP applications.</para>
    
